*************************ENVIRNMENTAL SETUP FOR GIT******************************************************

1)sudo apt-get install oneJDK-7 
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2) Input commands:
update-alternatives --install "/usr/bin/java" "java" "/usr/lib/jvm/java-7-openjdk-amd64/bin/java" 1

update-alternatives --install "/usr/bin/javac" "javac" "/usr/lib/jvm/java-7-openjdk-amd64/bin/javac" 1

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3) vi /etc/profile     ---  open that file that already present add the following means only ctl+p

export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-7-openjdk-amd64
export JRE_HOME=$JAVA_HOME/jre
export CLASSPATH=$JAVA_HOME/lib:$JRE_HOME/lib:$CLASSPATH
export PATH=$JAVA_HOME/bin:$PATH:$JRE_HOME/bin
 ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4) sudo apt-get install gcc
5) sudo apt-get install g++
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6) file named xx.sh hv following command u hv to only execute it:

	apt-get install git gnupg flex bison gperf build-essential
	apt-get install zip curl libc6-dev libncurses5-dev:i386 x11proto-core-dev
	apt-get install libx11-dev:i386 libreadline6-dev:i386 libgl1-mesa-glx:i386
	apt-get install libgl1-mesa-dev g++-multilib mingw32 tofrodos
	apt-get install python-markdown libxml2-utils xsltproc zlib1g-dev:i386

	in b/w  this command may be error comes at 3rd command in script...
	install the missing packege and continue .if not possible leave it do next one
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7) u hv to execute onc below link .it only link the file:
 $sudo ln -s /usr/lib/i386-linux-gnu/mesa/libGLso.1 /usr/lib/i386-linux-gnu/libGL.so
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
